article.description: Nick Shafnisky threw for four touchdowns, had another rushing and ran for 109 yards to send Lehigh to a 49-35 win over Lafayette Saturday afternoon in the season finale for both teams.
article.headline: Lehigh dominates Lafayette on way to 49-35 romp
article.linkText: Lehigh dominates Lafayette on way to 49-35 romp
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Nick Shafnisky threw for four touchdowns, had another rushing and ran for 109 yards to send Lehigh to a 49-35 win over Lafayette Saturday afternoon in the season finale for both teams. Shafnisky was 21 for 27 for 283 yards passing and averaged six-yards per carry on the ground. Lehigh (6-5, 4-2 Patriot League) took a 21-0 lead when Shafnisky hit Trevor Socarras, Derek Knott and Gatlin Casey for scores of 3, 5 and 5 yards, respectively. Lafayette's DeSean Brown scored the first of his three touchdowns to make it 21-7. Brown, however, would later have his fumble scooped up by Brandon Leaks, who ran it back 84 yards to put the Mountain Hawks up 42-14. Drew Reed threw for 278 yards and two touchdowns for the last-place Leopards (1-10, 0-6). Brown carried 35 times for 146 yards.
